  • node centrality()
    • degree: the number of edges connected to a given node (e.g.the number of friends an individual has in a social network)
    • strength: the sum of the weights of edges connected to the node
    • betweenness: the number of geodesic paths (shortest paths) that go through a given node

#       .
scenes_chars <- lapply(scenes, function(x) {
  chars <- gsub("^([a-zA-Z]+):.*$", "\\1", x[grep("^([a-zA-Z]+):", x)]) #       

  chars_actor <- c()
  for (char in chars) {
    if (char %in% love_actually_cast$speaker) {
      actor <- love_actually_cast$actor[which(char == love_actually_cast$speaker)]
      chars_actor <- c(chars_actor, paste0(char, "(", actor, ")"))
    }
  }
  return(chars_actor)
})
#        .  tm   document-term matrix   .
scenes_chars_ <- lapply(scenes_chars, paste, collapse = " ")
scenes_chars_ <- unlist(scenes_chars_)
scenes_chars_ <- scenes_chars_[scenes_chars_ != ""] #     
scenes_m <- DocumentTermMatrix(Corpus(VectorSource(scenes_chars_)), control = list(tolower = FALSE))
scenes_m <- t(as.matrix(scenes_m)) %*% as.matrix(scenes_m)
print(scenes_m[1:3, 1:3])
